 was born in there was three bedrooms - and downstairs there was - three, like a - a parlour we used to have, a sitting room and back kitchen. Well there were six rooms. Then we only had a few men then you see. Well afterwards we shifted to - no, we was t
h
irty-three first and then we shift to thirty-six. Then we went to number eleven, my father had - two houses, eleven and twelve, and he had them knocked into one. And the bedrooms was upstairs, and through the yard - or the wall that we could go around, ge
t around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Is that the house that you remember best of all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes, that - well it was -
