\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. Florrie, oh she's dead, yes, oh she lived - she went to live in Newport.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 There's only one girl you remember living in with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 And she slept with you, would she sleep in the same bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes, we had a double bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Where would she eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 With us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What would she call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh she only called me Edie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What did she call your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Mrs Purvell. Mr Purvell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 And your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Mr. Purvell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did your mother supervise all the work she did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes, oh yes, my mother - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did you feel that she was interested in you as a little girl?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 The servant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh she was all right, yes. She'd taken me out sometimes - the - Empire or - or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What would you call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 I used to call her Florrie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Was she allowed to have any time just to do what she liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Could she go out of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh they - yes, they used to go out - w
hen they used to have a - once a week off she used to have, one day, I - I believe every Sunday, and one day - one half day a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 She lived in with you because she happened to live in Newport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 But all the other girls you had were local were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did your mother sort of mind what she did when she went out or what time she came back, did she watch her like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh - oh she had - oh she had to be in by a certain time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did she give her any moral guidance, because you would have been very near the dock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh - well I don't think there was any call for it. No. There wasn't any call for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 How did the housework go, did she do it all, the girl or would your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No - my mo
ther used - used to do a lot, I used to do the washing when I got bigger, I - but my mother used to help a lot. We had them mostly for the scrubbing because my mother couldn't kneel much, she used to have rheumatic fever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You said you had a lady to do the washing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would she come every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No, she used to come twice a week. Two days a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would she have food with you when she came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What would you call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Mrs Friar her name was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What did she call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh they all called me Edie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Who made or mended the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well we had - I - I don't know at all who made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did your mother do any mending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would she make clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 She wouldn't make them, no, that's how I had all my clothes made in the dressmakers. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would a dressmaker come to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No, I used to go to her house. She lived in Spider Street, Mrs Tate - Miss Title her name was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Who did the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would he do it all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 All the meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
Mostly, but - if my father would go to - docks with men sometimes taking their clothes to the ships, my mother would do the cooking - in the afternoons. But always on a Saturday my father done
 the most of the - made pastry and everything. And he only had one hand. His hand - his right hand was off to there. From his wrist, from a - an accident in a saw mill in Canada. Before ever he came to England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 And he could do everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Do eve
rything with it, make bread, anything. He cut the boys hair, my mother used to tie a - a comb around his - his wrist there, and he'd comb them and cut - he had the power in his other hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 And there was nothing there at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Only a stump. Used to call it Joey when we was kids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What did you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh - only laughing, he used to laugh a lot with us. But if he hit you with it you'd know it. Oh my God. Hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What did you feel about it when your father had a hand like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well - we got used to it of course, we knew all about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You didn't think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Your father didn't do anything about your clothes, he didn't make anything or mend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh he didn't - never made any - bought everything that we wanted, boots or anything like that or anything we wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you have new clothes or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4217081\charrsid4983030  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Nothing second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4217081\charrsid4983030  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Where would they be bought when you had new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well there were plenty shops in the town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you go into Cardiff or would you have them from here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No - at Queen Street mostly my mother used to go to buy them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 When would you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Every holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Every holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 That'd be a few times a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Every holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 And - oh well, I was heavy on shoes. My father always bought our boots. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Where would you buy the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Town - at town, in town, yes. Oh there was just - used to be the shop that we used to go to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 When would you have new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Whenever wee need them. We always had Sunday shoes and day school. I know that because it was my job to clean them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 All the family's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes, clean all the shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 When would you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Every Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did you have jobs to do as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
Yes. Oh I had to - when I come home from school in the evening and I had to do - help with the back kitchen and clean the knives and forks. We all had something to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Any other jobs you'd do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh I - well then when - after I left school I used to do the washing for my mother. Because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about when you were at school, what sort of jobs did you do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh, little - just little - run some messages and little jobs round the house. Cleaning knives and forks and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about your other brothers and sisters, what about William, would he have a job to do at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well - oh a footballer he was. He was always a footballer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What did you think about that, you having to do the jobs and him going out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
I didn't half like it I tell you but I had to do it, you couldn't say yes or no to my father, or mother. Dare not answer them. Couldn't stop in the room if he was - talk - speaking to the - to women, you go in the room but he onl
y look at you and you get out quick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about Caroline, did she have any jobs to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
Oh well she didn't - she didn't live very long before she died. She died - I remember she had - pneumonia. Well didn't used to call it pneumonia then, used to call it - what - some - something in the lungs, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You don't know how old she was when she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
I couldn't tell you properly, I can remember my mother crying trying to put her new shoes on. But - of course we didn't go to the funeral, we were only young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would Robert have any little jobs to do around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh he was another outdoor too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 So the boys got away with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 He used to go - he used to go to the - to the pub where the - Bob Downey used to - they all - t
hey used to have horses, look after - he was always on a horse. The stable up there, like top of the street, Gladstone Street. He'd go around with my father's waistcoats on on top of his -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about Henrietta?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh well she - she used to - oh well, oh yes, she used to help but when she left school -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about when she was in school, did she have any little jobs to do like you had to do -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh yes, she had to do her share. I used to have to - I nearly brought her up because my mother was
 in bed - for - oh - not arthritis, no - rheumatism, she - gout, she had - used to have gout, mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You were ten years older than Henrietta?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 So you looked after her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 I had to look after her then when my mother was bad, she was awful bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 I was going to ask you did you help the younger children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you dress Henrietta?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Wash her and dress here, yes. And wash all her clothes, I wouldn't let nobody else do them, I used to do all her clothes. Wouldn't
 let the maid who used to come and wash. See my day's washing out on the line, all her little gingham frocks, and I used to iron them and - goffer the pinafores. I had to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would she help you in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh when she'd grown up, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about when she was a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh she'd run messages but she didn't do much work. She was pretty delicate, she was six months old before she was baptized, she was bad.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house, you mentioned he did all the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 He done - done most of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about the cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well I told you we had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Your father and mother didn't really do any cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No, not -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about washing up, the girls did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 The girls washed up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about making the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh well - father used to light the fire in the morning when he got up first. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about decorating the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well they always had a man to come in - to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Same thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Your father wouldn't do anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well he - couldn't really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Improvements to the house? Well if he only had the one hand -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Very handy with that you know, used to do a lot - he'd make little stools and that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 He was good like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 But he wouldn't do any repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh no. He couldn't get up there - with that one hand you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Had to be in bed - half past eight. From half past eight to nine at latest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My mother always saw - seen us to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 At what age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 After I left school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What age was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You told me you shared the bedroom with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 That was Henrietta was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. When she was a baby I used to look after - she used to sleep with me. That was before had Floorie, then we used
 to have the girls coming in every day. But this one that came from Newport you see she slept with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What became of Henrietta then, where did Henrietta sleep then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well we had a single bed then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well, that
 - down the stairs in - in the house. Number twelve. We used to - we had a big fireplace and we used to have - of course you'd no baths like we've got now, used to bath in there. Lock the doors up and curtains up, we'd light the fire, heat the water on th
e fire and bath in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you keep that room for the bathroom, would the bath be there all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You wouldn't use it for anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 In the - in the sitting room in a - our - our own, like the middle room.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 The middle room of number eleven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Where did your father cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What sort of cooking equipment, coal or gas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No, we had a range in the - in middle room, it was - no gas at that time. We had a range and a - fireplace in the kit
chen. And we'd plenty pots and saucepans and - plenty of - utensils of every - anything for our use.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 When would breakfast be eaten, what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 The men'd have theirs about nine. Nine. 'Course if - when we were going to school we'd have ours first
, before we went to school. Then the - the men'd be served. And my mother and father would have theirs about ten. After all of - it was over see, my mother used to stay in bed 'til ten, he wouldn't let her get up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 But when you were in school what would the arrangement be, who had breakfast with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 All the children together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 And your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh my father wouldn't have breakfast 'til my mother got up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 But who would make the breakfast for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 He'd make the breakfast for you children, you'd go to school, then he'd feed the men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Then after the men had gone your mother and he would have breakfast together, so there were three breakfast really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. Only on a Saturday when there was no school we were all together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 But you wouldn't have it with the men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh no. We dare not go in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 It was kept quite separate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. In fact he - he wouldn't let us in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 They were fed in the other part of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. We weren't allowed in that part where the men were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What did you usually have to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well - see now - Sunday morning we'd have salt fish and potatoes. Monday morning we'd have fry up and bacon. Tuesday morning have t
ripe and onions. Wednesday morning we'd have bacon and eggs. Thursday - sausage. Sausage and mash. And Fridays - my father wouldn't have no meat in the house, we all had to have fish Fridays. There wasn't no meat because - he wasn't a Catholic, but he - i
n Canada he was working in a - a - monks place - monast}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4217081\charrsid4983030 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
ry, and they were Catholics and of course they wouldn't eat no fish - no meat on a Friday, so he - he'd taken to the habit and he kept it up with us, we - up 'til now I won't eat meat on a Friday. We weren't Catholics though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What would you have to drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Tea or coffee, what we wanted. Mostly tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh always have good cooked dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You came home for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. Oh yes, my - my school was only round the corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Who would be there to have the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 And you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My father would - he might have had it sometimes with us, but if he was busy around the house he'd have it any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Your mother would have dinner with you though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What would you have for your midday meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Vegetables and meat. Different kinds of vegetables and - sweet after it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you have different food on certain days like on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh we'd have a - oh a big roast on a Sunday, we always had. Pork chops or - mutton chops and all that we'd have during the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You'd have fish on Friday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 And Friday we'd have - fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What would you have to drink with dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 We could have lemonade or - we could have - glass of water mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about the other meals, would you have an evening meal or would you have tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Have tea. Tea when we come from school at half past four we came home from school, we had tea at five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Who would have tea with you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My mother and father, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What did you have then for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well all kinds - all - have cakes more than - bread, cheese, I had - we always had plenty to eat. Plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about to drink for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you have another meal again then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
We'd have cup of - glass of hot milk going to bed, little biscuit or something like that, they would - he wouldn't give - we had nothing late. Then we never had - I don't know I never have late supper. I don't eat anything after my tea.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did your mother of father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My father did, yes, but he knocked it after we had the boarders you know 'cos he didn't have the time see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 But you used to have it before you had the boarding house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would your father or mother make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No, we'd - not that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Vegetables? Make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My mother made pickles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 We didn't have much of a garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did they buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you have tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Fresh vegetables. I - and - and - we never had tinned fruit. No, we had fresh fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did you keep any livestock for the family, like hens or a pig?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 We had chickens. Had - but - I - we had some chickens so - we used to get lovely eggs from the chickens, we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well - all of us, go and feed them like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Sunday, Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, most every day. Always on a Saturday we'd have soup. Yes. Well, meat in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 It was only Friday you wouldn't have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Only Friday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you have any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Poaching? No. Where we going to got poach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Only once. That was one time of the - mother and father - big - strike - the big coal strike, 1926, we had less then than we'd ever had.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did your father have more food than the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 We had to eat what was given to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
Well if - you couldn't eat it they wouldn't force you. Wouldn't force you. But was always wholesome food. But they wouldn't force - if you'd had enough you'd had enough, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt could you ask someone to pass it to you or would you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh we can ask. Ask.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. And get it too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 And sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 When you was - all finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Can you remember how you sat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. My father'd sit one end, my mother'd sit there - 
I'd sit close to my mother and my brother and sister up there, and my sister would be up there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 How was the meal served? Would your mother serve it, or your father, who would serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My mother'd serve it when we were together. But my fa
ther - my mother always put the - she put our dinners up, they wouldn't put the vegetables, you help yourself. She'd put them all out, yes. And then if we wanted more we could have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What order would you be served in, who would she serve first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Serve the girls first. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Where did the younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh the babies used to sit in the high chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Who would feed them, you remember Henrietta as a baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 I had to feed her. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 When were they able to join in the family meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 When they could stand - walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You mentioned that the servants ate with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did they have different food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No, they had the same. Same, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 She was a wonderful mother. Wonderful. I only wi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4217081\charrsid4983030 
sh she was alive today. Good wo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 man. She was very affectionate, she was a good mother. Very fond of all her children, she never made - more of
 one than she did of the others. Nor my father either. We were all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would she kiss you goodnight or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh yes. Wonderful mother. If everyone had one like her they'd have nothing to worry about. My father was good too to her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Was he easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would he show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
Oh yes. The only thing with my father he was strict. He was very strict on where you went and where you go you know, if I'm out - go out anywhere ask - I went to ask my mother 
she said you'll have to ask your father. And if he said yes I'd go and if I didn't - if he said no that was it. When he said no he meant no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 She wouldn't tell you whether to go or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No. No. Ask your father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 If you had any worries could you share them with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
Well I never had much to say in - like anything worrying - but my mother was - well she was a goddess to me. Very sympathetic. She was a goodmother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You had to mind your manners. Yes. You had to be very mannerly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 We had to - respect them. The eldest - used to - look out for little ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 They hoped us to be good children, and good wives and mothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. Everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh my father hated it. I never heard my mother or father swear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Not allowed in the room, never mind - join in. Never mind the join in, we weren't allowed in the room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 That - run away. Clear out of their way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you get punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 I've had it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Who would punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Can you remember why, one occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh, it would - I hit my brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My father hit the two of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 How did you feel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 I cried, that's all. That's all I could do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What did he do, just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No, he took a cane. Yes. And he caned the two of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 On your hands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Across the back we had it. Beat the two of us, he said, now you can fight again
. We didn't fight no more. I used to be bossy with him see. I would be bossy and they - they resent it - they'd resent it, you see, the - and I hit him and he hit me back and that was it - father hit the two of us so we fight - we didn't fight no more

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Was that only once, do you remember being punished more often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh no, not often. Very rare. Very rare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Were you ever punished by your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No. Mother never raised her hand to none of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 How did you feel about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
Oh I didn't like it. My - the most my mother would do, say now you're not going out, you're not going anywhere. The girls'd come for me to play out, no more no less, that was it, they'd have to go. Well that used to hurt me more than anything when the g
irls'd come for me. And today they wouldn't reigh you know, my parents - we were taught to respect everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you say that received the ideas about how to behave from both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
Oh both. Mostly. My mother was the - the most sympathetic but I - I wouldn't say anything that I didn't want my father to know, to him - I'd tell my mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 But you couldn't tell your father really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Do you think he played a more important part in teaching you how to behave and that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Than your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
He played - well one - not one more than another, on a Sunday you had to sit down and sing hymns with him. Sunday evening. He'd have a big book
 on the table specially and we had to be stuck there. Oh - three times church Sunday. And then sit down Sunday night and sing hymns - singing hymns with him. And go to church Sunday morning, Sunday school afternoon, church - Sunday evening, and then we'd 
have church again at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would your mother and father go with you to church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My father used to go, he was - mostly - chapel, used to - Baptist he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did your mother go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No, she didn't go then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh we'd have a party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you receive any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. Oh we always had a party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you have something special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Father used to make all the confectionary and he used to make a cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you have friends, guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
Yes. That goes back now for my brothers and sisters, I've - I've had their children and brought them up and done it for them now. I've got a nephew up there, I brought him up since he were two year old. And I'v
e done the same with his children now, when it's my birthday I have them down to tea with me. Make the cake. Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 So you used to have a nice birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. All of us did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Your father would make the cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day, how would you spend Christmas Day then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh we'd have - we'd all be together Christmas Day. We could have - we had a gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9905064\charrsid4983030 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 phone, the old battered gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9905064\charrsid4983030 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
phone, 'til had - we had a - music music box. We were all allowed to sing and that, we had a good day. Plenty to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did you have any musical instruments in the home, did you have a piano or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes, my sister learnt the piano. That was in later - later.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Not when I was a little girl, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 But you had a gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9905064\charrsid4983030 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 phone then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 A gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9905064\charrsid4983030 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
phone and a music box.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well I - I'm not bragging but I was a bit of a singer. And my sister was a good singer too. And she played the piano well too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You said your father used to sing on Sunday nights?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you make music together any other time as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No, unless - some of th
e men sometimes they - some used to play guitar and had a - if we'd had a - a party amongst theirselves they'd play for us or anything like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did your parents ever play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
Plenty of books. Hymn books, Bibles. But only books mostly that they have - I always got for good attendance at school and generally had a book - I've got packs - stacks of them there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you have any newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well we wasn't to allowed to read much newspapers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Comic papers, that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9905064\charrsid4983030 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 s all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My mother wasn't much of a scholar. My father was a good scholar.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Could your mother read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 She could read but she wasn't a great scholar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You don't remember seeing them reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My father but not my mother much, she wasn't much of a scholar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did they ever read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Father did. Out of the Bible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would they read to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 My father had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes, my sister. My mother's - brother died there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Can you remember what it was like, the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. Well it was the horse cars then, not - not motor cars, all horse cars. Oh yes, we had a good funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What was it like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
The - the bearers, and you see all - men mostly used to walk ahead. The bearers. Good funerals. Have the finest car. And my father had a big funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 That was later on of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Do you remember a funeral when you were a child? You don't remember your little sister being buried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. Little white coffin in front of the - carriage. The youngest one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you go to the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No, I've not been to - not when I was small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Who would attend the funeral?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Father and mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 It would be quiet would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Black, always black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 What about you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 We had - well I had - girls you know would have white dresses and black sash tie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Only my mother's relations used to live across to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Across the road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you see them often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You wouldn't go out otherwise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You wouldn't be taken out to visit anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh I used to go shopping with my mother. And then I had to go on my own after and do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You did mention that your father bought the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 He always bought our shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Would you go with him or would he buy them and bring them home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Always go with him. He used to take me with him if I - 'cos I always wore these - high legged \{BLANK\} boots. But
 they were right up - right high. He used to always take me up to measure them. And he'd buy the boots for the boys and all, he'd - and if we wanted any clothes otherwise he'd give us some money, say give it to your mother, let her go with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. Once. Once, I was a big girl then too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 
He went - he was - he was in the - the lodge, oh what's the name of it - I know I've got it - never used to drink, it was - there was a lodge where they took drinks a lot What did they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9905064\charrsid4983030 Odd fellow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 s?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes. And he was a \{BLANK\}
 there, and they had a big dance when I was - big - well young girl then, I were about fifteen. So he took me with him. And when - when they come along - when the
y come along with the drinks he said, none for her mind, I can always remember it. None for her mind, give her a lemonade. Well - I started getting - if I wanted to dance I - with anybody I'd have to get out of his way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You couldn't let him see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No, not with anybody. He was very - oh he was very strict, my father was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Wouldn't he let you dance with anybody at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No, not with anybody. There were - his friends out of the lodge, well that I could dance with them. No - no outsiders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 You couldn't pick anybody yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 So you remember that outing with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Do you remember any other outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh sometimes we used to go out - every year used to make a drive, you know, a c
oach drive, well it was brakes that time, horse brakes. We could go with them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Your father would organize it would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Who would go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Well all the neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 The street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Where would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Oh we've been to Porthcawl, no, not Porthcawl, we went to - where now - where that - ruined - church is. Tintern Abbey. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8550931 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Wye Valley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6162818 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11796586\charrsid4983030 Yes.
